02/11/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The campaign for the November 30th parliamentary elections officially began on Friday (October 31st). 
The vote will be the first in the country's history in which voters will be allowed to cast their ballots directly for specific candidates rather than for a political party. 
A total of 2,965 candidates are running for the 315 seats in the lower house and the 137 seats in the senate. 
Election officials announced on Friday that a total of 18.3 million Romanians are eligible to vote in the elections. 
(Gandul - 02/11/08; AP - 01/11/08; Rompres, Evenimentul Zilei - 31/10/08)
